FEEDEATER renders a Tumblr feed into HTML.

Does not require jQuery, but can use jQuery if it's around --
pass jQuery selectors or selector strings as the 'target' parameter,
use jQuery in custom renderers, etc.


Basic usage:

  <script src="tumblr-feedeater.js"></script>
  <script src="http://yourblog.tumblr.com/api/read/json"></script>
  <div id="tumblr-posts"></div>

  <script>
    // use old-style class invocation
    FEEDEATER.render_posts();

    // or new-style instance invocation
    var f = new FEEDEATER();
    f.render({target: 'tumblr-posts'});
  </script>

Advanced usage:

  See tumblr-feedeater.js source.

Testing:

  Load index.html to run Jasmine tests on tumblr-feedeater.js.


